The '10' button who can be actionned on keyboard with the key @{B}'/'@{UB}
allow you to (des)activated the 10 mode.
Le mode 10 n'a d'effet que lors de l'appui sur une touche-numéro:

If it is desactivated, the choosen sound will be hundreds+tens+@{B}new unit@{UB}

Else, the first number-key stay activated and manager is waiting for a
@{B}second@{UB} number-key.
the choosen sound will be hundreds+@{B}new tens and unit@{UB}.

The 10 mode is the mode activated by default.
